properties.headline: Winter Storm Warning issued February 8 at 7:32PM CST until February 9 at 6:00PM CST by NWS La Crosse WI
properties.description:
...Dangerous Travel Late Tonight into Sunday...

.Dangerous travel conditions are expected at times late tonight
into Sunday due to heavy snowfall. A heavy band of 8 to 10
inches of snow, with locally higher amounts possible, is expected
along and north of the Interstate 90 corridor. Snow amounts of 3
to 6 inches are expected to the north and south of this three
county wide band. Travel will go from difficult to dangerous in a
short amount of time Sunday morning as snowfall rates increase to
1 to 2 inches per hour. The worst conditions are expected between
4 AM and Noon Sunday.

* WHAT...Heavy snow. Snow accumulations of 8 to 10 inches. Much of
this snow will occur between 4 AM and 11 AM when hourly snow
rates will be in the 1 to 2 inch range. There may be a brief
period of freezing drizzle as the snow comes to an end on
Sunday afternoon.

* WHERE...Portions of southeast Minnesota.

* WHEN...From midnight tonight to 6 PM CST Sunday.

* IMPACTS...Travel will be dangerous at times.
properties.instruction:
If you must travel, keep an extra flashlight, food, and water in
your vehicle in case of an emergency.

The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER STORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM MIDNIGHT TONIGHT TO 6 PM CST SUNDAY
